tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated serum creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), all supporting possible renal dysfunction and/or tubular damage. HbA1c is low, indicating no chronic hyperglycemia. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Recommend further nephrological evaluation and assessment for possible acute or chronic kidney disease.
